      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Experimental validation — hemolysis index comparison against FDA benchmark data",
      "description": "Predicted normalized hemolysis index (NHI) compared against FDA-published experimental measurements for the generic centrifugal pump across five flow-speed operating points. Mean absolute percentage error of 8.3% across all conditions; maximum deviation 14.1% at 5 L/min / 3500 rpm, within the pre-specified acceptance band of ±20% NHI. Relative hemolysis index RH < 1 confirmed for all tolerance variants evaluated. Validation activities conducted using the same fluid (bovine blood, hematocrit 35±2%) and pump geometry as the COU.",
      "hasMetric": "Normalized Hemolysis Index (NHI), Relative Hemolysis Index (RH)",
      "acceptanceCriterion": "RH < 1.0; NHI deviation within ±20% of experimental reference"
